manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: SOFT + STRONG Bamboo's natural grass fibers produce a strong paper that is still soft for you and your Caboo! NATURALLY DERIVED Caboo Bamboo Baby Wipes are naturally derived and unscented. Ours contain no nylon or plastic fibers, no trees, and no harsh chemicals HYPOALLERGENIC Made with materials that are less likely to produce an allergic reaction - so you can feel good about using on baby's gentle skin. UNSCENTED Unlike many wipes, ours are free of additional scents, which can cause skin irritation.

PHLALATE FREE Phthalates are a group of chemicals used to make products more durable, at the cost of potential health risks. Our baby wipes are always phlalate free. ALCOHOL FREE No alcohol is present in our baby wipes. Alcohol is can be harsh to sensitive skin. PARABEN FREE Parabens are a group of compounds used as preservatives in products. We are proud to produce paraben free wipes. CHLORINE FREE Chlorine-free paper is an environmentally preferable alternative to paper bleached with chlorine.
The Importance of Bamboo Paper vs. Tree Paper

Zero Cut. One Planted. Choosing Caboo saves trees and replants them, too. Working with the U.S. Forest service, we plant a tree for every pound of paper sold. More trees means better air, water, habitat and chance to combat climate change. We believe most people want to do better by the Earth. But where to start? We started Caboo: two brothers, a wife and a friend. Wiping out forests along with a spill or a bum just didn't make sense to us. So we figured it out, building relationships with trusted farmers, retailers and folks along the way. Ten years and two kids later, we're even more committed to making tree-free the go-to. Daily decisions like choosing Caboo do make a difference. We and the forest thank you! The paper industry clear cuts 1,000,000 acres of North American boreal forest each year. While trees may be replanted (and re-cut) the forest is gone forever. But, Trees Grow Too, Right? Yes, but the complex ecosystem that is a forest is gone forever. A forest is biodiverse. Over time, it is populated by different species of plants, animals and other living things at all stages of growth. They depend on each other, creating a complex ecosystem our climate depends on. It can't be replicated. Big Paper basically replants tree farms: only 1 or 2 species of the fastest growing trees all planted at once so they can get cut down again. This is why tree-free matters. How is Caboo a more Earth-conscious choice than recycled paper? Bamboo and Sugarcane are grasses, not hardwoods. They both grow very quickly and, after harvest, grow back just as quickly. No replanting is necessary. Unlike trees, which can take up to 30 years to grow and mature, bamboo and sugarcane grow back as quickly as in three to four months. When a tree is cut, it never grows back. In addition, bamboo’s natural rhizome (root) network protects soil from erosion and retains moisture, and bamboo can grow in environments with depleted soil and little water. In fact, it actually returns nutrients to the soil; improving degraded areas. How Caboo gives back. It's not just the trees impacted. Bamboo vs. Trees Tree-Free > Reused Tree Paper

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Thick wipes, great for sensitive skin
reviews.reviewText: I use these to wipe my CPAP mask every morning - they have no scent and are amazing to use on a mask that touches my (sensitive) face for 8 hours a night. They are thick and sturdy and I've ordered them several times and will order more. These are the best wipes I've ever used.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars NO baby wipe should be flushed. Ever. This is a good product, contrary to some of these reviews.
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a sustainable wipe to keep from using cotton or microplastics. This is a little pricey, but good. I got unscented, so I can't speak to the scent. They do just what all baby wipes do--gently wipe. I am seeing lots of silly reviews on here about it not being flushable. I hate to break it to you--you shouldn't be flushing baby wipes, anyway, unless you want to ruin your septic or your plumbing. EVEN IF A PRODUCT SAYS IT'S FLUSHABLE, YOU SHOULDN'T BE FLUSHING IT. Google it and gaze your eyes on the massive fat and buttwipe bergs clogging city sewers.These are eco friendly because they are derived from bamboo. Not because you can flush them. It's a sustainability issue--bamboo grows fast and is easily replaceable.This is a good product and the company delivered it just when they said they would.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great wipes, minor comments
reviews.reviewText: We love them, they’re soft and moist, and their eco friendly. Don’t mind the extra cost to have our diaper changes have less of a toll on the environment, but:1. It’s hard to sometimes pull out just one wipe, leaving you with 2-3 in your hand and not easy way to put them back in.2. There are no fully biodegradable diapers out there, and we don’t have 2 diaper pails. Also Seattle municipality told us to throw them as trash. So we end up as a result with a biodegradable product that is not sent to a composte facility. The environment still benefits but mostly from the sourcing and production of the wipes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gentle cleansing power on a strong wipe!
reviews.reviewText: I have had a subscription for these wipes for a while now. I’ve never noticed any unpleasant odors. I use these wipes for EVERYTHING. Aside from typical baby wipe use I also keep these in my kitchen to clean up my kids after eating. These are gentle enough that I can wipe food off my toddlers face without bothering skin. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love love love
reviews.reviewText: After trying several types of wipes, some of which being compostable since I wanted to be more eco conscious, I came across these. It was love at first wipe. These large wipes help me so I'm not reaching into the wipe pack a million times like with smaller ones, they don't tear, they don't stink, they're soft, they hold the moisture in even inside the warmer, and they get the deed done while being eco friendly!I rarely review products unless I truly love them, or hate them, but in this case it's love.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the very few biodegradable wipes
reviews.reviewText: It was important to me that I found eco friendly wipes. And that turned out to be a big challenge. These are biodegradable and made from bamboo which I love. They have a light, very clean and pleasant smell. I will be buying more when I run out. These are a little pricey, but that's to be expected. And its alright because we use cloth diapers and wipes so only need these when we are put and about. This one pack has lasted over 3 months.
